  • Understanding Cloud Computing
      • Benefits: Reduced cost, scalability, reliability
      • Service models: IaaS, PaaS, SaaS
      • Deployment models: Public, Private, Hybrid

  • Virtualization
      • Abstract hardware
      • VM, Hypervisor (Type 1 bare metal, Type 2 hosted)
      • Vagrant

  • IaaS
      • Fundamental infrastructure
      • Benefits: Cost, scalability, control
      • Uses: Web servers, Big Data

  • PaaS
      • Development & deployment environment
      • Reduced complexity, speed of delivery

  • SaaS
      • Complete applications (email, office...)
      • Subscription model

  • Serverless Computing
      • Function-based, event-driven
      • AWS Lambda, Google Cloud Functions, Azure Functions
      • Knative, OpenFaaS

  • Configuration Management Tools
      • Ansible (agentless), Puppet, Chef, Salt

  • Build and Release Tools
      • Terraform, CloudFormation, BOSH

  • Key-Value Pair Stores
      • etcd, Consul KV, ZooKeeper

  • Logging and Monitoring Tools
      • Elasticsearch (ELK), Splunk, Prometheus

  • Cloud Computing Cost and Budgeting
      • Pricing, Billing, Governance (AWS Organizations, Trusted Advisor...)


